                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_631-item1">
                     <locus>(fol. iv verso)</locus>
                     <author key="person_54553752">Richard of Thetford</author>
                     <title key="work_4332">Ars dilatandi sermones</title>
                     <note>(summary)</note>
                     <rubric>Istis modis potest quis habundare in themate</rubric>
                     <incipit>Primo per qualemcunque termini notificationem</incipit>
                     <note>This is ascribed in an almost contemporary list of contents on fol. iv to 'frater Ricardus de Tefforď, as a 'Summa de modo predicandi'; cf. Charland, <title>Artes praedicandi</title> (1936), 79.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem class="#biblia" n="2" xml:id="MS_Bodl_631-item2">
                     <locus>(fol. 1)</locus>
                     <title key="work_10468" type="desc">Biblical concordance 'De vitando consortio'</title>
                     <note>(<bibl type="repertory"><ref target="http://www.repbib.uni-trier.de/cgi-bin/rebiIndex.tcl?ac=searchlist&amp;tlnr=10084">Stegmüller, <title>Bibl.</title> 10084</ref></bibl>)</note>
                     <note>The first title is 'De uitando consorcio ... malorum', the second 'de celeri conuersione a seculo', and a conspectus of the whole precedes. This is no doubt for a preacher's use.</note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="3" xml:id="MS_Bodl_631-item3">
